name: Wisata Gelar River
address: Batuagung, Jembrana, Jembrana Regency, Bali 82218, Indonesia
review 1: Pretty refreshing in a hot, sunny day. The water is very clean. It's good to come here with family or friends. It's fun to cross that bridge on scooter and listen to different tunes that it makes.
review 3:
Bit of a roller coaster ride to get to on a narrow road, which is in great condition though.

Parking space is quite limited, but not many cars as most people use motorcycles, which is recommended, especially since that's what the suspended will allow.

Lots of "boiling pots" to choose from to bathe in near the bridge but one could easily hike up, or down river to find a quiet spot.

There's a nice deep pool downstream from the bridge at the bottom of the trail going down from the opposite side of the parking lot entrance.

The water is very clean as is to be expecte,  even though some people wash their clothes.
review 4: Good place to cool down. The river has just the right temperature. Location in the jungle.
